<font color="#FF0000">TALKIN BOUT THE NAM</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15 23:48:46 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Sitting in a VFW hall in 1970, I was listening to some old World War II vet<br>
 carrying on about the glories of fighting in the Big One, the last good war.<br>
He turned to my buddy, who like me was just back from the Nam, and he said<br>
&quot; How about some stories about Viet Nam and the fighting over there.&quot;<br>
Which prompted my buddy to ask:<br>
&quot; Do you know what the difference is between a war story and a fairy tale?&quot;<br>
&quot; Why no, I guess I don't&quot; came back the answer.<br>
Which prompted my buddy to reply &quot; That's cause there is no difference.&quot;<br>

<p><code>-- Billyphil1  (Anonymous) </code><p>


